title: Man extradited to Sydney and charged with child sex offences allegedly spanning two decades - 9news.com.au
text:
Man extradited to Sydney and charged with child sex offences allegedly spanning two decades By 9NEWS The man arrived from Heathrow Airport this morning. (9NEWS) 
A 72-year-old man has been extradited from the UK to Sydney and charged with multiple child sex offences allegedly spanning two decades. 
He arrived in Sydney this morning and has since been charged with “multiple alleged historic child sex offences”, police said in a statement. The man will face court today. (9NEWS) 
The offences allegedly occurred in the 1970s and 1980s in Sydney, and relate to one alleged victim. 
Detectives had been investigating the allegations for years, and last week travelled to the UK to arrest the man. 
He will appear at Waverley Local Court today. © Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
